This paper deals with natural language inference (NLI) models and their susceptibility to dataset bias. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes a debiasing algorithm based on residual fitting, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves designing learning algorithms, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses benchmark datasets, which may involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves training models, which may involve neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
